= The <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> Is Banned!

Wilhelm Frick of the Interior Ministry has announced an emergency measure, effectively banning the <span style="color: #700000;">**KPD**</span> after conveniently "uncovering" evidence of a planned revolution involving the <span style="color: #700000;">**RFB**</span>â€”including several warehouses allegedly stocked with weapons. A raid on a <span style="color: #700000;">**Communist**</span> party office has also produced a so-called plan to establish a new "<span style="color: #750e0e;">Soviet Germany</span>" in the aftermath of the revolt.

According to the government, these plans were to be set in motion in protest against Schleicher's unconstitutional adjournment and the mass arrests of <span style="color: #700000;">**Communist**</span> deputies that followed. Only the state's last-minute intervention, they claim, has saved Germany from violent revolt.

But Schleicher and the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">Nazis</span> cannot be trusted. They could just as easily have planted the evidence to manufacture a pretext for crushing the <span style="color: #700000;">**Communists**</span>.

